main event: A civilian observed a single unidentified object in the sky over Winter Park, Florida on April 15, 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed visually and aurally for approximately 3 minutes., The object was described as having a metallic reflective surface., The object was shaped like a ball and exhibited a bright flash of light., The observation was made from a school bus window by a boy who had previously encountered teasing for his interest in UFOs., The report concludes that the object remains unidentified with insufficient data for classification.
sighted object: one unidentified object in the sky, shaped like a ball
witness description: a boy on a school bus who is interested in UFOs
